newsitem.title: USA: Republican Brownback wins Kansas Senate seat.
newsitem.headline: Republican Brownback wins Kansas Senate seat.

text.p: Kansas selected freshman Republican congressman Sam Brownback over Democrat Jill Docking to fill the remaining two years of Sen. Bob Dole's term, major television networks reported Tuesday.

Docking, a stockbroker and moderate who favored abortion rights, would have been the first Democratic senator from the state since the Great Depression. Brownback, a conservative, had defeated Dole's temporary replacement, politically moderate Sen. Sheila Frahm, in the primary.
